---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const effective = 'April 24, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for nikkyamresh.github.io — what data is collected, how it is used, and your rights."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-prose px-4 pb-20 pt-12 sm:px-6 sm:pt-16 lg:px-8">
    <header>
      <p class="font-mono text-2xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-accent">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 font-mono text-sm text-text-subtle">Effective {effective}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="prose prose-invert mt-10">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains what information is collected when you
        visit <strong>nikkyamresh.github.io</strong> (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;), how
        it is used, and the choices you have. The Site is operated as an
        individual by Nikky Amresh, based in Bangalore, India.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information collected directly</h2>
      <p>
        The Site itself is a static website and does not require you to
        create an account or submit a form. I do not run my own analytics,
        tracking, or advertising on the Site.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you email me, your email address and the contents of your message
        are stored in my email inbox so that I can reply.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Information collected by hosting and third-party services</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Hosting</strong>. The Site is hosted on GitHub Pages.
          GitHub may collect standard server logs (IP address, user agent,
          referring URL, timestamp) as described in the
          <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Privacy Statement</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Fonts and assets</strong>. Fonts are bundled locally via
          <code>@fontsource-variable</code> and are not loaded from a
          third-party CDN at runtime.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Sponsorship</strong>. If you sponsor my work, payments are
          processed by GitHub Sponsors and their payment processor (Stripe).
          I receive limited information from GitHub (such as your GitHub
          handle, sponsorship tier, and amount). I do not receive or store
          your payment-card information. See the
          <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/sponsors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Sponsors documentation</a>
          and <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stripe Privacy Policy</a>
          for details.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How information is used</h2>
      <p>Information is used only to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Operate, maintain, and secure the Site.</li>
        <li>Reply to emails you send me.</li>
        <li>
          Fulfill sponsorship perks (such as sending an occasional update
          email or listing sponsors on a public page, if you opted in).
        </li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        I do not sell, rent, or trade personal information. I do not use
        your information for advertising.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        The Site does not set tracking cookies. A single technical entry in
        browser <code>localStorage</code> is used to remember your theme
        preference (light/dark) across visits; it is stored only in your
        browser and is not transmitted.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Emails are retained in my inbox for as long as reasonably useful to
        continue the conversation, and then archived or deleted. Information
        about sponsorships is retained for as long as required by GitHub,
        Stripe, and applicable tax and accounting law.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct,
        or delete personal information that I hold about you. To exercise
        these rights, email
        <a href="mailto:nikkyamresh8@gmail.com">nikkyamresh8@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Rights related to payment information are handled by GitHub Sponsors
        and Stripe under their respective privacy policies, as I do not
        store that data.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Children</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is not directed at children under 13, and I do not
        knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        This policy may be updated from time to time. The
        &ldquo;Effective&rdquo; date at the top of this page reflects the
        most recent revision.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy can be sent to
        <a href="mailto:nikkyamresh8@gmail.com">nikkyamresh8@gmail.com</a>,
        or see the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <a href="/" class="font-mono text-sm text-accent no-underline hover:underline underline-offset-4">
        ← Back to home
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
